      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This addition to the Rowland Egger papers spanning the
         years 1945-1971 consists of ca. 100 items. These papers
         contain mainly reports, memoranda, and letters received or
         produced by Egger while serving on the President's Task Force
         on Government Reorganization, July-November, 1964.</p>
         <p>There are three letters from President Lyndon Baines
         Johnson to Egger thanking him for working on the Task Force
         and expressing appreciation for work done in Bolivia, prior to
         the organization of the Task Force.</p>
         <p>Drafts drawn up by Egger and Donald K. Price, Chairman of
         the Task Force, were prepared to set a basis for discussion
         during the Task Force meetings. Also included are
         electrostatic copies of the revised and final drafts of the
         report of the President's Task Force on Government
         Reorganization.</p>
         <p>There is an electrostatic copy of a press release from the
         Office of the White House Press Secretary dealing mainly about
         four major domestic problems: education, health, conservation
         of natural resources, and farm policy. Many of the problems
         stated in the press release were studied by the Task
         Force.</p>
         <p>One article of interest in the collection not dealing with
         the President's Task Force was a memorandum submitted by
         President Richard M. Nixon's Advisory Council on Executive
         Organization on 
         <title render="italic">Natural Resources</title>.</p>
      </scopecontent>
